3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The dynamic power algorithm used in the paper can be considered as a control system, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the spectral efficiency and network capacity, which are related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss security, the use of self-interference cancellation techniques can have implications for security, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security.
